  "text": "[4] Whether EAC mesoscale variability is predominantly an intrinsic local instability of the boundary current system or due more to remote forcing was considered by [CITATION_1] . They found no evidence that EAC mesoscale variability is coherent with planetary wave activity entering the region from the southwest Pacific east of Lord Howe Rise. Rather, they concluded that westward phase propagation from a region of elevated mesoscale energy immediately to the north and east of the EAC separation was actually the signature of northeastward energy propagation (consistent with short Rossby waves) emanating from a source associated with local instability processes in the separation region. Details of the nature of this instability were not determined.",
